{
  "texts": [
    "-AI engineer- [G34].",
    "Developing responsible AI was seen as building positive relations between organisations and human beings by minimising inequality, improving well-being, and ensuring data protection and privacy.",
    "However, when it comes to the relative importance of ethical principles, it was a divided house.",
    "An AI practitioner who participated in a study [G11] thought that AI systems must be fair in every way.",
    "Likewise, some participants in another study [G8] also thought that fairness issues in AI systems must not only be minimised but completely avoided, highlighting the importance of developing a fair AI system."
  ]
}